A £2.7MILLION community centre has been opened in Kirkintilloch. £2.7m centre is opened by council leader A £2.7MILLION community centre has been opened in Kirkintilloch.The centre, in Hillhead, was built as part of a wider regeneration project by East Dunbartonshire Council.It replaces the former Hillhead Community Centre, which has stood in Meiklehill Road for more than 80 years.The new facility was opened by council leader Rhondda Geekie. 